                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.512351 Double/231: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-16T10:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 16, 1935—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 16—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>209. Foreign Minister last evening told me that on Friday next he has arranged to
                    appear before Finance Commission of Senate to urge ratification of double
                    taxation treaty and is practically certain of persuading members to report
                    favorably.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
